# Translation Guidelines

## Rule Description

When you are adding or modifying text in Filament components or any user-facing elements, use translations located in `lang/{locale}` directories.

## Rule Explanation

Using translations ensures centralized management of translations, making the application consistent and maintainable across different languages.

## How to Fix

Use keys like `module::resource.fields.name.label` in language files.

## Examples

### Correct

* Use keys like `module::resource.fields.name.label` in language files.

### Incorrect

* Hardcode text or use `->label()` method directly in components.

